title.narrative: China: Guangdong Social Security Integration and Rural Worker Training

description.narrative: The objective of the Project is to enhance portability of social security data and beneficiary entitlements, and to strengthen the skills base and employment prospects of urban and rural workers in Guangdong.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Loan Agreement Schedule 2, Section B, 1 | Description :The Borrower shall cause the project Implementing Entityto carry out the Project, and cause the Project Schools to carry out their Respective parts of the Project, in accordance with theProject Implementation Plan in a manner satisfactory to the Bank and shall not amend, suspend, or waive the said plan or any partthereof without the prior written agreement of the Bank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Loan Agreement Schedule 2, Section I D,1 | Description :The Borrower shall cause the PIE to carry out, andensure that the Project is carried out, in accordance with the provisions of the Environment Codes of Practice, and except as theBank shall otherwise agree in writing, the Borrower shall not assign, amend, abrogate, or waive, or permit to be assigned, amended,abrogated, or waived, the aforementioned, or any provision thereof. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Loan Agreement Schedule 2, Section II, A | Description :Prepare semi-annual project progress report no laterthan March 15 and Sept. 15 each year, in form and substance satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :SemiAnnual

Finance Agreement :Loan Agreement Schedule 2, Section II, B,2 | Description :Prepare interim un-audited financial reports for theProject no later than March 15 and Sept. 15 each year, in form and substance satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :SemiAnnual
Finance Agreement :Loan Agreement Schedule 2, Section II, B,3 | Description :To submit audit reports to the Bank. | Frequency:Yearly
Finance Agreement :Project Agreement Schedule Section I E,2(a) | Description :Annual work and budget plan submitted to the WorldBank for no objection by December 15. | Frequency :Yearly
